        "body": "@jakirkham, that does sound like a useful feature. Is this typically for multidimensional FFTs, batched 1D FFTs or for a single large 1D FFT?\r\n\r\nI don't have experience with performing a single 1D FFT in a distributed fashion, but the references @martindurant provided sound like they may be related to the approach described in the [multi-GPU 1D cuFFT docs](https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cufft/index.html#oned-mgpu-data-organization). I would have to think about it, but it seems plausible that Dask could do something similar, possibly with some restrictions on the chunk sizes.\r\n\r\n@leofang added multi-GPU 1D FFTs to CuPy last year. It seems based on [this comment](https://github.com/cupy/cupy/pull/2644#issuecomment-558835428) that it is useful mainly when the data is too big to fit in memory. ",
