        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "It looks like @moble implemented an out-of-core FFT based on Cormen's approach (linked by @martindurant above) in https://github.com/moble/dask_fft.\r\n\r\nIt seems like the problem solved by mpi4py-fft and FluidFFT are a different case from the out-of-core approach, and instead deal with efficient domain decomposition of multi-dimensional transforms (e.g. slab or pencil decompositions in 3D). Unless I am mistaken, at any given time, one axis is contiguous in memory and standard FFTs are applied along that axis. Then a transpose is performed so that a different axis is contiguous in memory for the next dimension, etc.\r\n",
